    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6}{t^{2}-12t+32}-\frac{t-2}{t^{2}-12t+32}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{t-4}, t\ne 8</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6}{t^{2}-12t+32}-\frac{t-2}{t^{2}-12t+32}} 
      \amp = \frac{{6-\left(t-2\right)}}{{t^{2}-12t+32}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6-t+2}}{{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-t+8}}{{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-\left(t-8\right)}}{{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{t-4}, t\ne 8}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t-8</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {8}</m>.</p>
</solution>
